post_text: So proud and honored to be a Mustang! I am surrounded by amazing staff, students, and parents everyday 🥰
shared_text:
Superintendent Kathy Hoffman
October 23, 2019 at 5:30 PM ·

Happy Wednesday! Our #NationalPrincipalsMonth celebration continues with Lauren Arnold, the principal at Gilbert Arts Academy and Mari Jo Mulligan, the principal at Thunderbolt Middle School, L.H.U.S.D.

At Gilbert Arts Academy, Lauren Arnold demonstrates the value of leading through kindness. Ms. Arnold holds her teachers and students to high expectations, which they gladly meet because of her love and respect for their community.

Nominated by a fellow Thunderbolt educator, Ms. Mulligan's nomination says it all:

"Mari Jo does such a phenomenal job at making school not only safe but fun! She truly cares about every student, staff, and parent. Her heart is on love and kindness, regardless of the situation. I deeply admire her and am proud to be a part of her team!"
